---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="SocialProof for Auto Repair Shops — Reviews That Fill Your Bays | SocialProof" description="Auto repair shops: customers are skeptical before they hand over their keys. SocialProof helps you collect and display genuine testimonials that turn skeptics into regulars.">
  <main>
    <section style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 1.5rem;">
      <h1 style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:1rem;">
        Social Proof for Auto Repair Shops
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.2rem;color:#555;margin-bottom:2rem;">
        "Is this mechanic going to rip me off?" is the first thing every new customer wonders. The answer — the only answer that actually works — is proof from other customers. SocialProof helps you collect genuine testimonials and display them on your website so new customers arrive already trusting you.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">Why trust is the #1 problem in auto repair marketing</h2>
      <p>Auto repair has a perception problem. People expect to get overcharged or sold repairs they don't need. The shops that win long-term are the ones that have visible, specific, credible customer stories. Not a generic "5 stars" on Google — actual words from actual customers describing what got done and how they were treated.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem;">A SocialProof widget on your homepage, your services page, and your estimate form page works 24/7 to answer the question "can I trust these people?" before you even open the door.</p>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">What great auto repair testimonials say</h2>
      <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li><strong>Honesty:</strong> "They called me before doing any extra work and explained exactly what was needed and why."</li>
        <li><strong>Fair pricing:</strong> "Quoted $180, final bill was $165. No surprises."</li>
        <li><strong>Expertise:</strong> "Three other shops couldn't figure out the noise. These guys diagnosed it in 20 minutes."</li>
        <li><strong>Speed:</strong> "Dropped off at 8am, picked up by noon. Same day on a complex job."</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-top:2.5rem;">How it works</h2>
      <ol style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
        <li>After pickup, text your customer a SocialProof link (works great in your existing follow-up text)</li>
        <li>They write a quick testimonial — no app, no account, just a form</li>
        <li>You approve it and it goes live on your site immediately</li>
        <li>Every new visitor sees a wall of real customer experiences before they even call</li>
      </ol>

      <div style="background:#f8f9fa;border-radius:12px;padding:2rem;margin-top:2.5rem;">
        <h3 style="font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Free forever for 1 active widget</h3>
        <p style="color:#555;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Start turning happy customers into testimonials today. No credit card, no trial period. Upgrade when you need more widgets or features.</p>
        <a href="https://socialproof.dev/signup" style="display:inline-block;background:#0070f3;color:#fff;padding:0.75rem 1.75rem;border-radius:8px;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none;">Start free</a>
      </div>

      <section style="margin-top:3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.4rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Frequently asked questions</h2>

        <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
          "@context": "https://schema.org",
          "@type": "FAQPage",
          "mainEntity": [
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "How can I get more reviews for my auto repair shop?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "The most effective approach is asking right after pickup — that's when satisfaction is highest. SocialProof gives you a share link you can text customers immediately after they pick up their car. One click takes them to a simple form with no account required."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "Where should I display testimonials on my auto shop website?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Homepage, services page, and anywhere near a 'call us' or 'book an appointment' button. These are the high-anxiety decision points where trust signals do the most work."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "What's the difference between Google reviews and testimonials on my own website?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Google reviews live on Google — you can't control their placement, format, or how they're surfaced. Testimonials on your own site appear exactly where you need them, in the format you choose, and they contribute to your site's SEO directly."
              }
            }
          ]
        })}>
        </script>

        <details style="border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:8px;padding:1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
          <summary style="font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;">How can I get more reviews for my auto repair shop?</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;color:#555;">The most effective approach is asking right after pickup — that's when satisfaction is highest. SocialProof gives you a share link you can text customers immediately after they pick up their car. One click, no account required.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:8px;padding:1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
          <summary style="font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;">Where should I display testimonials on my auto shop website?</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;color:#555;">Homepage, services page, and anywhere near a "call us" or "book an appointment" button. These are the high-anxiety decision points where trust signals do the most work.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:8px;padding:1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
          <summary style="font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;">What's the difference between Google reviews and testimonials on my own website?</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;color:#555;">Google reviews live on Google — you can't control their placement or format. Testimonials on your own site appear exactly where you need them and contribute to your site's SEO directly.</p>
        </details>
      </section>
    </section>
  </main>

